00040 void IterativeRobot::SetPeriod(double period)
00041 {
00042     if (period != 0.0)
00043     {
00044         // Not syncing with the DS, so start the timer for the main loop
00045         m_mainLoopTimer.Reset();
00046         m_mainLoopTimer.Start();
00047     }
00048     else
00049     {
00050         // Syncing with the DS, don't need the timer
00051         m_mainLoopTimer.Stop();
00052     }
00053     m_period = period;
00054 }

00083 void IterativeRobot::StartCompetition()
00084 {
00085     // first and one-time initialization
00086     RobotInit();
00087     
00088     // loop forever, calling the appropriate mode-dependent function
00089     while (TRUE)
00090     {
00091         // Call the appropriate function depending upon the current robot mode
00092         if (IsDisabled())
00093         {
00094             // call DisabledInit() if we are now just entering disabled mode from
00095             // either a different mode or from power-on
00096             if(!m_disabledInitialized)
00097             {
00098                 DisabledInit();
00099                 m_disabledInitialized = true;
00100                 // reset the initialization flags for the other modes
00101                 m_autonomousInitialized = false;
00102                 m_teleopInitialized = false;
00103             }
00104             if (NextPeriodReady())
00105             {
00106                 DisabledPeriodic();
00107             }
00108             DisabledContinuous();
00109         }
00110         else if (IsAutonomous())
00111         {
00112             // call AutonomousInit() if we are now just entering autonomous mode from
00113             // either a different mode or from power-on
00114             if(!m_autonomousInitialized)
00115             {
00116                 AutonomousInit();
00117                 m_autonomousInitialized = true;
00118                 // reset the initialization flags for the other modes
00119                 m_disabledInitialized = false;
00120                 m_teleopInitialized = false;
00121             }
00122             if (NextPeriodReady())
00123             {
00124                 AutonomousPeriodic();
00125             }
00126             AutonomousContinuous();
00127         }
00128         else
00129         {
00130             // call TeleopInit() if we are now just entering teleop mode from
00131             // either a different mode or from power-on
00132             if(!m_teleopInitialized)
00133             {
00134                 TeleopInit();
00135                 m_teleopInitialized = true;
00136                 // reset the initialization flags for the other modes
00137                 m_disabledInitialized = false;
00138                 m_autonomousInitialized = false;
00139             }
00140             if (NextPeriodReady())
00141             {
00142                 TeleopPeriodic();
00143             }
00144             TeleopContinuous();
00145         }
00146     }   
00147 }

00159 bool IterativeRobot::NextPeriodReady()
00160 {
00161     if (m_period > 0.0)
00162     {
00163         return m_mainLoopTimer.HasPeriodPassed(m_period);
00164     }
00165     else
00166     {
00167         return m_ds->IsNewControlData();
00168     }
00169 }
